		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.29]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=thermopylae&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Is there an autocircle of sorts for the solo'ing bard?&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /> <br />Also, do you other bards out there use macro key's for songs to be able to sing a couple and then hit a new macro? If you do please post an example.  Thanks. <br /> <br />kleff&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >1 Replies</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td>

		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sat, Nov 13th 3:55 AM2004 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=1100218534477781074&num=1&post=1&replyto=1100336119173894379"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1100336119173894379></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=247125"><span id="Scholar">Jiggidyjay of the Seven Seas</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1950 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.20]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I answered the auto-circle question in the other thread, so you can check there for that. As far as twisting macros: <br /> <br />You can assign macros for twisting. If you want to twist songs 1,2,3 and 4 in your gems and bind them to hotkeys, the macros would look something like: <br /> <br />HOTKEY 1 <br />/cast 1 <br />/pause 30 <br />/stopsong <br /> <br />HOTKEY 2 <br />/cast 2 <br />/pause 30 <br />/stopsong <br /> <br />ETC, ETC <br /> <br />You'd need to play with the number after the /pause to get the timing right. It's the length of the pause in 10ths of a second. <br /> <br />You can put 2 songs on one macro, but that creates problems. I don't use macros for twisting. Think of it like this: macros are like driving an automatic and double tapping is like driving a manual. You work less with the automatic, but you have more control with the manual. The same applies with twisting.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> <br />The real downside to using the macros is once a macro is started, you can't type anything else/use any other hotkeys until the macro is finished. This means if you fizzle, you have to wait the whole 3 seconds or so that the macro is running before you can try again. The same goes for using other social macros, like your /assist key or /incoming key. It also applies to typing, so no burst typing (typing while a song is casting. You only have 3 seconds, but it's better then nothing). Due to these limitations, it will be very hard for you to ever accomplish a 4 song twist, or even maintain a 3 song twist reliably. Our fizzle rate is just too high. <br /> <br />SOE did put an autotwist feature on test a while ago, called /melody. It would allow you to set up a 4 song twist and just hit one key to start it. The downside was that once a song fizzled, you'd have to restart it yourself, and you'd have to tell it which song to start on. That means 4 hotkeys, /melody 1,2,3,4 /melody 2,3,4,1 /melody 3,4,1,2 and /melody 4,1,2,3. You'd also have to pay very close attention to see which song it fizzled on. Shortly after putting it on test though, they removed it for &quot;tweaking&quot; and we haven't heard anything since... <br /> <br />Most, if not all, of your barding questions can be answered by browsing the guides and newbie forums at <a href="HTTP://www.eqdiva.ecom" title="HTTP://www.eqdiva.ecom" target="akztarg">EQDiva</a>. It's an awesome site, and as long as you at least TRY to find the answer to your questions either in the guides or forums before you start posting them in the general forums, people will generally be pretty helpful.</p>
